# Medical Agentic System Architecture

This document describes the high-level architecture of the Explainable Multi-Agent Medical Report Understanding System.

## Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Users and API Layer
    User((User / Dashboard)) <--> |HTTP GET / POST| FastAPI[FastAPI App / main.py]

    %% Data Sources
    subgraph Data Layer
        CSV_NOTEEVENTS[(NOTEEVENTS.csv)]
        CSV_DIAGNOSES[(DIAGNOSES_ICD.csv)]
        CSV_LABEVENTS[(LABEVENTS.csv)]
    end

    %% Data Loading
    CSV_NOTEEVENTS --> DataLoader[MIMICDatasetLoader]
    CSV_DIAGNOSES --> DataLoader
    CSV_LABEVENTS --> DataLoader
    
    DataLoader --> EnrichedReport[Enriched Report State]
    
    %% Model Manager
    subgraph Local LLM Ecosystem
        FlanT5{{google/flan-t5-large}}
        BioGPT{{microsoft/biogpt}}
        BioClinicalBERT{{BioClinicalBERT Classifier}}
    end

    %% Orchestrator & Agents
    FastAPI --> Orchestrator[Orchestrator]
    Orchestrator --> Flow[SequentialAgentFlow]
    EnrichedReport -.-> Flow
    FlanT5 -.-> Flow
    BioGPT -.-> Flow
    BioClinicalBERT -.-> Flow
    
    subgraph Multi-Agent Pipeline
        direction TB
        A1(ClinicalAgent) --> |clinical_summary| A2(RiskAgent)
        A2 --> |risk| A3(ExplainabilityAgent)
        A3 --> |explanation| A4(VerificationAgent<br/>Pre-Verification)
        A4 --> |verification_preliminary<br/>confidence_gate| A5(RecommendationAgent)
        A5 --> |recommendation| A6(JustificationAgent)
        A6 --> |justification| A7(VerificationAgent<br/>Final Verification)
    end
    
    Flow --> Multi-AgentPipeline
    Multi-AgentPipeline --> FinalState[Final Validated State]
    
    %% Evaluation
    subgraph Evaluation
        Eval[Evaluator]
        Baseline[BaselineSummarizer]
    end
    
    FastAPI --> |/evaluate| Eval
    Eval --> Baseline
    FinalState --> Eval
    Eval --> Results[(results.csv)]
    
    FinalState --> FastAPI
```

## Component Details

1. **FastAPI ([main.py](file:///c:/Users/chira/OneDrive/Desktop/medical-agentic-system/backend/main.py))**: The primary entry point exposing REST endpoints (`/cases`, `/analyze/{case_id}`, `/evaluate`) and the dashboard UI.
2. **Dataset Loader ([dataset_loader.py](file:///c:/Users/chira/OneDrive/Desktop/medical-agentic-system/backend/dataset_loader.py))**: Merges multiple MIMIC-III data sources (`NOTEEVENTS`, `DIAGNOSES_ICD`, `LABEVENTS`) into an enriched data context.
3. **Orchestrator ([orchestrator.py](file:///c:/Users/chira/OneDrive/Desktop/medical-agentic-system/backend/orchestrator.py))**: Manages the SequentialAgentFlow, running sequential inference steps across the multi-agent pipeline while applying strict state validation.
4. **Agents**:
   - **ClinicalAgent**: Extracts diseases, findings, and key observations, combined with the BioClinicalBERT classification.
   - **RiskAgent**: Computes risk levels.
   - **ExplainabilityAgent**: Creates patient-friendly plain-language summaries.
   - **RecommendationAgent**: Generates actionable next steps depending on pre-verification confidence.
   - **JustificationAgent**: Justifies the given recommendations based on risk and explanations.
   - **VerificationAgent**: Checks for contradictions and enforces safety guidelines, both midway and at the end of the flow.
5. **Evaluator ([evaluation.py](file:///c:/Users/chira/OneDrive/Desktop/medical-agentic-system/backend/evaluation.py))**: Re-runs the baseline over the entire dataset to compare agent generation vs local baselines and assesses FKGL (readability), word count, QA scores, and metrics.
